{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018P2LuSdLZwCDnaAvntvEk2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-27\n     2→\n     3→**Sprint:** Epic 14 completion session\n     4→**Duration:** ~20 minutes\n     5→**Stories completed:** 14-4, 14-5, 14-6 (all verified and marked done)\n     6→**Epic status:** Epic 14 — DONE (all 7 stories complete)\n     7→\n     8→---\n     9→\n    10→## 1. Session Summary\n    11→\n    12→Three stories were verified and marked done in this session, completing Epic 14:\n    13→\n    14→- **14-5** (stack-aware-verify-dockerfile) — Tier A quick validation. Proof already existed with 10/10 PASS. Two precondition issues found and fixed before `codeharness verify` passed: stale AGENTS.md missing stats.ts entry, and stats.ts at 1.14% coverage (18 tests written to fix).\n    15→- **14-6** (subagent-status-ownership-time-budget) — Tier A quick validation. Proof already existed with 10/10 PASS. `codeharness verify` passed immediately.\n    16→- **14-4** (observability-backend-choice) — Unit-testable verification via subagent. ALL_PASS (10/10 ACs). 20 tool calls in the subagent, with one wasted Write (wrong proof format) and an overly broad grep.\n    17→\n    18→## 2. Issues Analysis\n    19→\n    20→### Category: State management\n    21→- **`state set` does not trigger YAML regeneration.** The `state set` command writes to `sprint-state.json` but does not regenerate the derived `sprint-status.yaml`. Only `writeStateAtomic` (called by certain internal paths) does the regen. This caused multiple fix attempts and confusion about whether state was actually persisted.\n    22→\n    23→### Category: Stale documentation\n    24→- **AGENTS.md for `src/commands/` was missing `stats.ts` entry.** The `stats` command was added in a prior session but the AGENTS.md doc was not updated. This caused a verification precondition failure.\n    25→\n    26→### Category: Test coverage gap\n    27→- **`stats.ts` had 1.14% coverage.** The command was shipped without tests in a prior session. Had to write 18 tests to bring it to acceptable levels before verification could pass.\n    28→\n    29→### Category: Workflow gap\n    30→- **Proof documents existed for 14-5 and 14-6 but stories were stuck at \"verifying\".** The proofs were generated but nobody ran `codeharness verify` to validate them and transition the story state. Stories sat idle until this session picked them up.\n    31→\n    32→## 3. Cost Analysis\n    33→\n    34→**Cumulative project costs** (all epics, all time):\n    35→\n    36→| Metric | Value |\n    37→|--------|-------|\n    38→| Total API-equivalent cost | $556.06 |\n    39→| Total API calls | 4,098 |\n    40→| Average cost per story | $3.25 (140 stories) |\n    41→\n    42→**Token breakdown:**\n    43→- Cache reads: $347.42 (62%) — dominant cost, expected for long-context sessions\n    44→- Cache writes: $123.43 (22%)\n    45→- Output: $85.04 (15%)\n    46→- Input: $0.16 (0%)\n    47→\n    48→**Phase breakdown:**\n    49→- Verification: $318.51 (57.3%) — most expensive phase by far\n    50→- Orchestrator: $98.81 (17.8%)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01WzV7cQxz9ekS4NphgGe8EL","session_id":"053c3102-7d57-462f-ac8f-5337a6c67a30","uuid":"a9797b1e-c50a-4cbc-931b-7e7a508732c0","timestamp":"2026-03-27T16:29:52.750Z"}
